We are looking to read the data from a 3 dimensional mapping on solidity using assembly 
Example : `mapping (address => mapping (address => uint256)) private _allowances;`

We know reading a two dimensional array could be done with the code below

`function getStorageValue(uint num, uint slot) public view returns (address result) {
    assembly {
        // Store num in memory scratch space (note: lookup "free memory pointer" if you need to allocate space)
        mstore(0, num)
        // Store slot number in scratch space after num
        mstore(32, slot)
        // Create hash from previously stored num and slot
        let hash := keccak256(0, 64)
        // Load mapping value using the just calculated hash
        result := sload(hash)
    } `

But failed to figure out 3 dimensional arrays.

To any Dev who knows how to do it, please share us your knowledge
